  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I-- of course, the-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I don't remember whether my very first trip into that courtroom was the first court reporter's turn, as we say, of the day, which would be before they actually started the proceedings.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That I do not remember, whether it was the first turn or whether I went in.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a rotating system with six court reporters going into the courtroom for, as I remember, it was either-- we started out at half-hour turns at a time.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we relieved that reporter who was in there at the end of a sentence by an understanding, a tap on the shoulder or whatever, and that reporter got up and left.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we did this on a revolving basis all day long.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we-- I would be back into the courtroom, and then toward the end of the day, we-- we went in for 15-minute periods to cut the time, so that that transcript could be finished more quickly.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But I do remember the-- there was a balcony built in the courtroom for the-- the people who were admitted, just the general audience.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But they had to be cleared to get into that courtroom.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When-- from when we finished that one turn, left, we walked past the prisoner's dock, close enough to touch Karl Brandt, the first defendant in the box, or Hermann Goering, in the case of those reporters.",
      "word_count": 36
    }
  ],
